 IAM Guidlines and best practices

 -Dont user the root account except for AWS account setup
 -One physical user = One AWS user
 -Assign users to groups and assign permissions to groups
 -Create a strong password policy
 -Use and enforce the use of multi factor auth(MFA)
 -Use access key for programatic acces (CLI/SDK)
 -Audit permissions of your account using IAM Credentials report & IAM

 -Never share IAM user & acces keys
